stories_text_raw:
As a system administrator, I want to set up logging with a basic configuration, so that I can monitor and debug the system.
As a developer, I want to improve logging, so that I can troubleshoot issues more effectively.
As a user, I want to be able to create different types of users, such as AgencyUser, Developer, FABSUser, and BrokerUser, so that I can manage access and permissions.
As a user, I want to be able to add and retrieve pages in the UI, so that I can customize the user interface.
As a user, I want to be able to add and retrieve submissions in the FABS system, so that I can manage submissions.
As a user, I want to be able to add and retrieve data in the FPDS system, so that I can manage data.
As a system administrator, I want to be able to process deletions for a given date, so that I can maintain data integrity.
As a designer, I want to redesign the resources page to match the new Broker design styles, so that I can improve the user experience.
As a tester, I want to report on user testing results, so that I can evaluate the system's usability.
As a developer, I want to move on to round 2 of DABS or FABS landing page edits, so that I can continue improving the system.
As a developer, I want to update the FABS sample file to remove FundingAgencyCode, so that I can ensure data consistency.
As an agency user, I want to ensure that deleted FSRS records are not included in submissions, so that I can maintain data accuracy.
As a developer, I want to update the FABS validation rules to account for rule updates, so that I can ensure data quality.
As a developer, I want to add GTAS window data to the database, so that I can improve data analysis.
As a developer, I want to manage and cache D files generation requests, so that I can optimize system performance.
As a developer, I want to prevent duplicate transactions from being published, so that I can ensure data integrity.
As a developer, I want to provide FABS groups that function under the FREC paradigm, so that I can improve data analysis.
As a user, I want to be able to get a human-readable error message based on an error code, so that I can troubleshoot issues more effectively.
As a user, I want to be able to validate a FABS submission and receive a list of error messages, so that I can ensure data quality.
